annotationA: Phosphoserine phosphatase; Catalyzes the last step in the biosynthesis of serine from carbohydrates. The reaction mechanism proceeds via the formation of a phosphoryl-enzyme intermediates (By similarity)
annotationB: GH03305p; NAD binding; phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; Belongs to the D-isomer specific 2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase family
